From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v24 - ps4_bridge mode_fixup forces 1080p60

v23 confirmed the bridge IS being fully programmed:

  ps4_bridge_pre_enable: cq_exec returned 20  (success)
  ps4_bridge_enable: MN864729 main seq cq_exec=20  (success)
  ps4_bridge_enable: END

But DRM was passing mode 1400x1050 (probably from lightdm's X
server defaults), so the GPU's DP transmitter was programmed to
output 1400x1050 timing while the MN864729 bridge was configured
for VIC 16 (1080p60).  Mismatch -> bridge can't decode the signal
-> HDMI stays dark.

Add ps4_bridge_mode_fixup() which overwrites adjusted_mode with
the canonical 1920x1080@60Hz timing (mode_1080p struct already
defined in this file).  Runs from the atomic_check phase via
drm_bridge_chain_mode_fixup so the rest of the pipeline (encoder,
crtc) is programmed for 1080p, matching the bridge.

If v24 works:
- "ps4_bridge_mode_fixup: incoming 1400x1050 -> forcing 1920x1080@60"
  logged
- GPU outputs 1920x1080@60 over DP
- Bridge converts to HDMI 1920x1080@60
- Monitor lights up

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -780,12 +780,32 @@
 	return 0;
 }
 
+/* v24: force the GPU's adjusted mode to 1080p60 regardless of what
+ * userspace requested.  We confirmed in v23 that the bridge IS being
+ * fully programmed for VIC 16 (1080p) but DRM atomic was passing
+ * mode=1400x1050 which the GPU then output -- a mismatch with what the
+ * bridge expected, so HDMI stayed dark.  Overwriting adjusted_mode here
+ * forces the GPU to output 1080p, matching the bridge config. */
+static bool ps4_bridge_mode_fixup(struct drm_bridge *bridge,
+				  const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
+				  struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
+{
+	struct ps4_bridge *mn_bridge = bridge_to_ps4_bridge(bridge);
+	pr_info("ps4_bridge_mode_fixup: incoming %dx%d -> forcing 1920x1080@60\n",
+		mode->hdisplay, mode->vdisplay);
+
+	drm_mode_copy(adjusted_mode, &mode_1080p);
+	mn_bridge->mode = 16;	/* CEA VIC 16 */
+	return true;
+}
+
 static struct drm_bridge_funcs ps4_bridge_funcs = {
 	.pre_enable = ps4_bridge_pre_enable,
 	.enable = ps4_bridge_enable,
 	.disable = ps4_bridge_disable,
 	.post_disable = ps4_bridge_post_disable,
 	.attach = ps4_bridge_attach,
+	.mode_fixup = ps4_bridge_mode_fixup,
 	.mode_set = ps4_bridge_mode_set,
 };
 
